gomodel:SYNGO_146  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Using immuno- electron microscopy it is shown that PKC delta is present in the postsynaptic cytosol. No knockout control is provided. As control, the antibody was pre-absorbed against the immunizing peptide.\n\n10/3/2017 Pim:\n-Fig17E is guess this EM picture is difficult to asses (by me). Authors conclude: \"Axon terminal (A) establishing multiple synaptic specializations (arrowheads) with a PKCG-i (PKC) dendrite (De)\". Dendritic labeling close to synapses (arrow) is considered as \"presynaptic\".. Experimental description: Male CD/Sprague-Dawley rats (300-350g) were anesthe-tized with tribromoethanol(2.5 pg/lOO g body weight), and colchicine was injected into the lateral ventricle (Merchen-thaler, '90)." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-7620-2704" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-1558-1958" ;
        dc:date           "2017-03-10" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_146" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

